A Foreign Office spokesman said: 'Two British nationals were among those killed in yesterday's attack in Kabul.

'Next of kin have been informed. Consular staff in Kabul are in close contact with the employer of the deceased.

'Our thoughts are with the families of those who died, ISAF personnel, contractors, Afghan forces and civilians. We stand ready to provide the consular assistance needed to their families.'

The armoured personnel carrier, known as a Rhino, was travelling on a four-lane road frequently used by Nato forces in a south-western section of the city.

In addition to those killed in the convoy, three Afghan civilians and one policeman died as a result of the attack with eight other Afghans, including two children, wounded, officials said.

